Genitalia. Surstyli turned ventrally, both with two projections at the end; epandrium elongated; ST8 extending to the right, membranous area large, almost reaching upper edge of ST8 (
Fig. 19H
). Ventrally on the base of SS and on SES ca. 10 hairs on each side; gonopods asymmetrical, both with ridges, OG longer; hypandrium with distal part (lobes) turned; phallic guide with membranous parts at the end covered by microtricha; phallus long, coiled, trifid (
Fig. 19K
); ejaculatory apodeme flat, fan-shaped (can be linear); sperm pump simple, flat, with two projections at the end (
Fig. 19J
). In lateral view PG has a hook pointing towards SS; SES present, although connection to GP is no clear; 
PH
with supporting structure (
Fig. 19L
